Looking at just the last 80 years, or since the end of WWII this actually continues to hold true, the Democratic parties nominees have an additional \~3 years on Republican nominees on average. What does this say? Democratic nominees sure love to hang around on the Supreme Court for a while!


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
supreme_presidents |>
  dplyr::filter(party != "Other" & nominated >= as.Date("1980-01-01")) |>
  dplyr::mutate(tenure = terminated - nominated) |>
  dplyr::group_by(party) |>
  dplyr::summarise(mean_tenure = paste0(mean(tenure, na.rm = TRUE), " days")) |>
  dplyr::ungroup() |>
  gt::gt() |>
  gt::cols_label(
    party = "Party of President at Time of Nomination",
    mean_tenure = "Avg. Tenure"
  ) |>
  DGThemes::gt_theme_duncan()
```

